# x86-64 Assembly Control Flow & Calling Convention Cheat Sheet

## Basic Function Structure

### Executable

```asm
.intel_syntax noprefix
.global _start

_start:
    ; code

    mov rax, 60
    xor rdi, rdi
    syscall
```

### Shared Library Function

```asm
.intel_syntax noprefix
.global solve

solve:
    ; code
    ret
```

---

# Linux Syscalls

| Syscall | rax |
| ------- | --- |
| read    | 0   |
| write   | 1   |
| open    | 2   |
| exit    | 60  |

## write(fd, buf, size)

```asm
mov rdi, 1      ; stdout
mov rsi, buffer
mov rdx, size
mov rax, 1
syscall
```

## exit(code)

```asm
mov rdi, 0
mov rax, 60
syscall
```

