# Function Calling Convention (SysV x86-64)

## Arguments

| Argument | Register |
| -------- | -------- |
| 1st      | rdi      |
| 2nd      | rsi      |
| 3rd      | rdx      |
| 4th      | rcx      |
| 5th      | r8       |
| 6th      | r9       |

## Return Value

```text
rax
```

Example:

```c
foo(1,2,3);
```

```asm
mov rdi, 1
mov rsi, 2
mov rdx, 3
call foo
```

---

# Returning Values

## return x;

```asm
mov rax, rdi
ret
```

Equivalent:

```c
long solve(long x)
{
    return x;
}
```

---

# cmp + setz

## if (a == b)

```asm
cmp rdi, 42
setz dil
```

Result:

```text
dil = 1 if equal
dil = 0 otherwise
```

---

# Conditional Jumps

## if (a != b)

```asm
cmp rdi, 42
jne fail
```

## if (a == b)

```asm
cmp rdi, 42
je success
```

Pattern:

```asm
cmp rdi, 42
jne fail

success:
    mov rdi, 0
    ret

fail:
    mov rdi, 1
    ret
```

---

# Loops

Pattern:

```asm
loop:
    ; work

    cmp something, something
    je done

    jmp loop

done:
```

String comparison:

```asm
loop:
    mov al, [rsi]
    cmp [rdi], al
    jne fail

    cmp al, 0
    je success

    inc rdi
    inc rsi

    jmp loop
```

