# Caller-Saved Registers

These may be destroyed by a function call:

```text
rax
rcx
rdx
rsi
rdi
r8
r9
r10
r11
```

Save before call:

```asm
push rax
push rcx
push rdx
...
call func
...
pop rdx
pop rcx
pop rax
```

---

# Callee-Saved Registers

Must be restored before returning:

```text
rbx
rbp
r12
r13
r14
r15
```

Pattern:

```asm
push rbx
push r12
push r13
push r14
push r15

; modify them

pop r15
pop r14
pop r13
pop r12
pop rbx

ret
```

---

# Stack Rules

## Push

```asm
push rax
```

Stores value on stack.

## Pop

```asm
pop rax
```

Restores value.

### LIFO

```text
Last In
First Out
```

Example:

```asm
push rbx
push r12

pop r12
pop rbx
```

Correct.

